Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%post
    # Update package list and install Python tooling.
    apt-get update
    apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends python3 python3-pip
    apt-get clean
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

    # Install pytest for the grading framework.
    python3 -m pip install --no-cache-dir pytest

    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    # Prepare the initial filesystem state required by the assignment.
    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    # Create the working directory structure.
    mkdir -p /home/user/pen_test

    # Populate /home/user/pen_test/targets.txt with the exact IP list.
    cat >/home/user/pen_test/targets.txt <<'EOF'
192.168.0.10
192.168.0.11
192.168.0.12
EOF

    # Ensure world-readable permissions as required by the tests.
    chmod 755 /home/user
    chmod 755 /home/user/pen_test
    chmod 644 /home/user/pen_test/targets.txt

%labels
    Author penetration-test-setup
    Description "Base image for mini vulnerability-pipeline assignment"

%help
This container provides the initial state for the penetration-testing
automation task. It includes:
  • pytest (for the grading harness)
  • /home/user/pen_test/targets.txt with the required IP addresses  
No other artefacts are pre-created.